Parents, teachers and other stakeholders have commended Gombe state Government for introducing Radio lessons for Senior Secondary school students in the state. Recall that the state Ministry of Education had recently commenced lessons on radio stations for SS 1, SS 2 and SS 3 students of the State.
The virtual learning system was designed to make up for academic losses for students due to the the closure of schools as a result of the coronavirus pandamic.
In an interview, a parent, Malam Tijjani Muazu commended the state Governor, Alhaji Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya for approving the Radio lessons which he said will go a long way in stemming the learning loss by having families re-engage with the process of learning during the covid-19 pandemic. He said, the lessons which run Mondays to Saturdays every week are very interesting and incisive, adding that his two children always tune in to the relevant stations to benefit from the broadcast. A secondary school teacher, who craved for anonymity also lauded the programme but advised that a television version of the initiative be introduced.
